  "prompt": "Why the users of Quora are so politically correct?",
  "response": "Quora's user base tends to be more politically correct due to several factors:\n\n1. Moderation policies\n- Strict community guidelines\n- Emphasis on respectful communication\n- Content can be flagged/removed if deemed offensive\n\n2. User demographics\n- Often educated, urban, professional users\n- Typically more liberal-leaning\n- Higher awareness of social sensitivities\n\n3. Platform design\n- Rewards for well-written, nuanced answers\n- Encourages detailed, thoughtful responses\n- Downvotes for inflammatory content\n\n4. Social signaling\n- Users want to appear intelligent and considerate\n- Politically correct language seen as sophisticated\n- Desire to maintain positive reputation on platform\n\n5. Self-selection\n- People who enjoy detailed, measured discussions\n- Those comfortable with academic/professional tone\n- Less likely to engage in confrontational debate\n\nThese factors create an environment where users tend to be more careful about language and presentation, often prioritizing perceived politeness and inclusivity.",
